# CODEOWNERS — required-reviewer routing for the highest-risk paths.
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Ownership here is enforced by branch protection's "Require review from
# Code Owners" rule. The maintainer set is identical across all branches.

# Release provenance ledger. The legitimate write path is the release
# build pipeline (synthesized at staging time, not committed by hand).
# Any PR that adds or modifies it manually must be reviewed — that
# is the spoof vector if an attacker tries to forge a release record.
RELEASE-PROVENANCE.json      @JVB-Consulting/maintainers

# CI workflows + reusable Actions. Workflow drift is the top supply-chain
# risk: a single PR that adds a malicious step or swaps an Action SHA
# can exfiltrate secrets or alter what ships. Require explicit
# maintainer review on every change.
.github/workflows/*          @JVB-Consulting/maintainers

# This file itself — protect the protection.
.github/CODEOWNERS           @JVB-Consulting/maintainers
